5:
Status report, Mother Love. Our
enforcers are currently engaged in
combat with hostiles.
8:
Paradigm Break Company?
*sigh* How meddlesome, but
expected nonetheless. Have we
received any backup from other
Noxel affiliates?
12:
They should be arriving shortly. Shall
I guide them to the other enforcers?
15:
Proceed. Although most of them are
synthetics, it still is a shame to
sacrifice them.
21:
Mother Love. I have intel that the
PBC forces are merely a diversion.
24:
I know. It seems Bulleta and her new
friends are on their way to see me
again.
27:
Do you think I made the right
decision here?
29:
Your judgment is absolute, Mother
Love. We will move our focus away
from the Noxel forces.
35:
I was just hoping that perhaps... I
was mistaken.
38:
Then it would seem that we are no
longer necessary.
44:
All DAN employees, including the
synthetics and myself—we remain
at your disposal.
45:
Nothing more than resources to be
used and deployed at your
discretion.
46:
Data suggests that the winning play
here would be to redistribute the
enforcers and ignore the distraction.
Knowing this...
52:
And are you questioning my
judgment?
54:
I wouldn't dream of it. Merely a
confirmation.
56:
However, Mother Love... If you were
hoping for another outcome—one
that did not involve our meddling...
57:
All you have to do is give us the
word.
59:
And we shall retreat or regroup as
you wish.
63:
No, no, Conductor. I must have had
a lapse in judgment.
65:
We will continue the operation as
originally planned—together.
68: That is a relief to hear.
69:
It is of utmost importance that the
perpetual night never ends. For that
is our mission—our duty.
71:
Please pardon me for doubting your
judgment. I will see to it that our
intruders are taken care of.
75:
Radius, continue to protect Mother
Love.
81: I cannot bring happiness to anyone.
83:
This is all I am capable of—as long
as I remain the wretched being I am.
85:
There's no way I can carve out a
future of my own... not like Bulleta.
87: Is everything all right, Mother Love?
90:
Conductor... Why did the directors of
Noxel create me in the form of a
human?
92:
If I had just been a synthetic, I
wouldn't have had to suffer like this.
95:
Mother Love. Your mental state
seems to be deteriorating. Shall I
schedule a therapy session?
99:
That won't be necessary. I actually
have a favor to ask of you, Radius.
102:
I cannot leave my cage, but you...
You still have a shot at freedom. So
be free.
107: That is up to you to decide.
109:
However, I DO have one last order
for you. Leave this facility, and once
you are out... discard any
association you have with me.
113:
This is goodbye. Take care of
yourself, Radius.
121: You made a mistake coming here.
124:
That right? And whose orders are
you here on?
126:
Nobody's. Coming here was my
decision.
128:
I should have finished you when I
had the chance.
130:
The World Flipper, was it?
If only I had noticed its presence
sooner, then...
133:
Then Love would've continued to act
entirely in your interests, right?
138:
You've seen it, haven't you? What
awaits you beyond this point. The
sheer power she possesses.
140:
And you still wish to proceed even
with this knowledge?
143:
Why does it have to be that
complicated?
147:
I want to show my friend what the
sky looks like—nothing more,
nothing less. And if I gotta fight a
few knuckleheads along the way, so
be it!
150:
Then allow me to simplify things as
well. My mission is to exterminate
you.
154:
Identifying target... Otherworldly
enemy
Brute forcing limit breaks...
162:
I exist to perpetuate this eternal
night for Mother Love.
164:
And if I must crush your dreams
along the way, so be it!
